postcontent:
Savage Model 11/111 FXP3 in .270. This rifle was taken on in trade. It has an internal 4rd magazine and is tapped for mounts. It is in good condition with a bit of surface rust on the barrel, but otherwise a nice rifle. I'm not sure on the value, so shoot me a fair offer.

1931 vz.24 in 8mm. This rifle is in wonderful condition for 80+ years old. Better yet, this rifle has no import marks, and is a full numbers matching rifle. An ultimate for the Mauser or Czech collector. I doubt there is a better one out there. The sling appears to be original as well. $400

1937 Mosin Nagant 91/30 in 7.62x54r. This is an Izhevesk pre-war manufacture which appears to be matching. The floorplate is forced matched however. All in all one of the better looking Mosins I've run across. $200

Yugo M24/47 Mauser in 8mm. This appears to be a refinished stock as it is very smooth and in good condition. The barrel was likely replaced during overhaul and rarely shot as the rifling is VERY crisp. The handguard does have the common crack behind the rear sight, but has been arsenal repaired with pins. Despite the bore in excellent condition, I do have an extra barrel that can go with it. $275/w barrel, $250 without.

I also have about 100-120 rounds of 1940's Turkish surplus ammo in 8mm. The rounds are headstamped, and from a little research, these were some of the better years of production. I have shot the rounds in the vz.24, the brass does split, but I haven't had an issue. The ammo is surprisingly accurate at 100 yards and will ring plates. These will come on the original cloth bandoliers. $50
